# Redesign existing Figma mocks

Improve layout, hierarchy, richness **inside same brand**. Do **not** rebrand.

**Before `use_figma`:** `figma-use` + `figma-generate-design`. Sequential `use_figma`.

## Inputs

Figma URL; which page/section; what feels wrong (optional).

## 1 — Diagnose

- `get_screenshot` full page + weak sections; `get_metadata` for structure
- Score: hierarchy, layout variety, whitespace, color use, typography, richness, copy, components/states, imagery, mobile
- Map symptoms → root causes (flat → depth/vary sections; cluttered → whitespace/hierarchy; generic → theme decoration; weak CTA → accent/isolation; etc.)
- Present: screenshot, **keep** list, **fix** list, approach (full rebuild vs targeted). **Approve before edits.**

## 2 — Design DNA

Extract from file: color variables, text/effect styles, components, spacing rhythm, wrapper width, personality (radius, shadows, gradients). **Redesign uses same tokens.**

## 3 — Execute

**Full rebuild:** rename old page `[Name] (Previous)`; new page same name; rebuild sections using DS.

**Targeted:** rebuild weak sections by node id in place; verify auto-layout neighbors.

**Techniques:** stronger type ladder; accent only on key CTAs; layered cards/shadows; alternating section archetypes (split/full-bleed/centered hero; feature grid; alternating rows; testimonial; stats bar; CTA band; carousel/grid; timeline; pricing table; FAQ; logos; full-bleed image; signup); benefit headlines; hover states; intentional image ratios.

## 4 — Validate

Per-section screenshots; full-page before/after; cross-page still same family.

## 5 — Present

Before/after; what changed + why; prior saved as `(Previous)`; ask tweaks.

## Anti-patterns

Change palette/fonts/tokens arbitrarily; delete original without `(Previous)`; skip diagnosis; simplify instead of elevate; identical sections; lorem; drop mobile if file had mobile; new components before adapting existing.
